<refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imgaussianblur3" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
<refnamediv><refname>imgaussianblur3</refname><refpurpose>Apply Gaussian smoothing to a 3-D volume.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imgaussianblur3(volume)
out = imgaussianblur3(volume, sigma)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist>
<varlistentry><term>volume</term><listitem><para>Numeric 3-D scalar volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>sigma</term><listitem><para>Positive Gaussian standard deviation in voxels. Default is 1.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Double filtered volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Applies a separable native Gaussian kernel along rows, columns, and slices. Replicate boundary handling preserves constant volumes.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
volume = zeros(41, 41, 17);
volume(13:29, 13:29, 6:12) = 1;
noisy = volume + grand(size(volume, 1), size(volume, 2), size(volume, 3), "nor", 0, 0.15);
smoothed = imgaussianblur3(noisy, 1.4);
imshow3d(smoothed, "orthoslice");
]]></programlisting></refsection>
